{"warnings":{"parse":{"*":"The value passed for \"page\" contains invalid or non-normalized data. Textual data should be valid, NFC-normalized Unicode without C0 control characters other than HT (\\t), LF (\\n), and CR (\\r)."}},"parse":{"title":"Pr\u00e9cis du si\u00e8cle de Louis XV","pageid":50765100,"revid":849440650,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Voltaire_Precis_title_page.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Voltaire_Precis_title_page.jpg/220px-Voltaire_Precis_title_page.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/12/Voltaire_Precis_title_page.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"240\" data-file-height=\"320\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Voltaire_Precis_title_page.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Title page of a first edition, from the collection of the Voltaire Foundation in Oxford</div></div></div><p><i><b>Pr\u00e9cis du si\u00e8cle de Louis XV</b></i> (<i>Short history of  the Age of Louis XV</i>) is a historical work by the French philosopher and author <a href=\"/wiki/Voltaire\" title=\"Voltaire\">Voltaire</a>, first published in its own right 1768.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pearson_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pearson-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Celebrating the progress of <a href=\"/wiki/Age_of_Enlightenment\" title=\"Age of Enlightenment\">Enlightenment</a> ideas and the retreat of <a href=\"/wiki/Prejudice\" title=\"Prejudice\">prejudice</a>, it comments on cultural, economic and technological progress made in France during the reign of <a href=\"/wiki/Louis_XV_of_France\" title=\"Louis XV of France\">Louis XV of France</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pearson_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pearson-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Content\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Content</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pr%C3%A9cis_du_si%C3%A8cle_de_Louis_XV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Background\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The material for the <i>Pr\u00e9cis</i> had been previously been part of a history that Voltaire spent twenty years working on and which included <i><a href=\"/wiki/Essai_sur_les_m%C5%93urs_et_l%27esprit_des_nations\" title=\"Essai sur les m\u0153urs et l&#39;esprit des nations\">Essai sur les m\u0153urs et l'esprit des nations</a></i> (<i>Essay on the customs and spirit of the nations</i>) and <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Age_of_Louis_XIV\" title=\"The Age of Louis XIV\">The Age of Louis XIV</a></i>. The <i>Precis</i> was introduced in 1762 as an appendix within this larger work, but later published separately.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Content\">Content</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pr%C3%A9cis_du_si%C3%A8cle_de_Louis_XV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Content\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Voltaire comments on the trial of <a href=\"/wiki/Thomas_Arthur,_comte_de_Lally\" title=\"Thomas Arthur, comte de Lally\">Thomas Arthur, comte de Lally</a>; a case he had been following closely. Lally had been a successful military officer, and personally known to Voltaire. When Lally was involved at a military defeat, relinquishing the Indian town of <a href=\"/wiki/Pondicherry\" title=\"Pondicherry\">Pondicherry</a> to the English, his fellow officers blamed him. On his return to France, Lally was imprisoned without charge, put on trial in which he was denied a lawyer, and finally executed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-davidson_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-davidson-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> In his account of the case, Voltaire wrote, \"His character made him detested by all who had to do with him. But that is not a reason for cutting off a man's head. The briefs both for and against him, which I have read attentively, contain nothing but insults, and not the least proof.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-davidson_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-davidson-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <i>Precis</i> also praises the courage of the Corsicans in defending against the French at the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Ponte_Novu\" title=\"Battle of Ponte Novu\">Battle of Ponte Novu</a>. Voltaire writes:\n</p>\n<blockquote><p>The principal weapon of the Corsicans was their courage. This courage was so great that in one of these battles, near a river named Golo, they made a rampart of their dead in order to have the time to reload behind them before making a necessary retreat [\u2026] Bravery is found everywhere, but such actions aren\u2019t seen except among free people.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pr%C3%A9cis_du_si%C3%A8cle_de_Louis_XV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Pearson-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pearson_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pearson_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Pearson, Roger (2005). <i>Voltaire almighty: a life in pursuit of freedom</i> (1., U.S. ed.). New York: Bloomsbury. p.&#160;305. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781582346304\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781582346304\">9781582346304</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Voltaire+almighty%3A+a+life+in+pursuit+of+freedom&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=305&amp;rft.edition=1.%2C+U.S.&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=9781582346304&amp;rft.aulast=Pearson&amp;rft.aufirst=Roger&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APr%C3%A9cis+du+si%C3%A8cle+de+Louis+XV\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation bo